TextEditDelay.Name: Delay

TextEditMaxDownTime.Name: Max down time
TextEditMaxDownTime.Info: This value is used to avoid a full delay in case of a short leave from it's target state If you get an interlock that cuts the filament heating and you then clear this interlock before the number of seconds specified by this value has elapsed, you would only have to wait a reduced time to achieve the same filament temperature

TextEditDownTimeFactor.Name: Downtime factor
TextEditDownTimeFactor.Info: If this value is: 1.0 then a downtime of 30sec would result in a 30sec delay when trying to reach the target state 2.5 then a downtime of 30sec would result in a 75sec delay when trying to reach the target state Booth examples above are only valid if the MaxDownTime has not been exceeded
